#Text=The Detroit Pistons ( 9 - 23 ) defeated the New York Knicks ( 5 - 30 ) 97 - 81 on Friday at Madison Square Garden in New York .
#Text=The Pistons had a strong first half , out - scoring the Knicks 57 - 38 .
#Text=With the strong start , they were able to coast through the second half and secure a 16 - point victory .

#Text=The Pistons shot well in this one , going 50 percent from the field and 39 percent from the three - point line , while the Knicks went only 35 percent from the field and 42 percent from beyond the arc .
#Text=Brandon Jennings had himself a game Friday .
#Text=In only 24 minutes , Jennings went 11 - for - 17 from the floor and 4 - for - 8 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 29 points .
#Text=It was a nice bounce back game for him after scoring only five points against the Orlando Magic on Tuesday .
#Text=Jodie Meeks provided a big contribution off the bench .
#Text=He scored 15 points ( 6 - 13 FG , 3 - 7 3Pt ) in 25 minutes .
#Text=Meeks is coming off a 34 - point outing on Tuesday , so he continued to ride his hot hand and had another good showing Friday .
#Text=While he did n't have much of an offensive impact , Andre Drummond was a monster on the boards .
#Text=He finished with 20 rebounds , marking the second game in a row and fifth time this season recording at least 20 rebounds .
#Text=He 's now averaging 13 rebounds per game on the season .
#Text=Greg Monroe had 12 points and 10 rebounds of his own , giving him his tenth double - double of the season .
#Text=Without Carmelo Anthony , Amare Stoudemire or Samuel Dalembert in the lineup , the Knicks were really thin .
#Text=J.R.
#Text=Smith was about the only bright spot for them , as he went 8 - for - 20 from the field and 5 - for - 9 from the three - point line to score 22 points in 36 minutes .
#Text=He was in the starting lineup for only the fifth time this season , and he capitalized on his opportunity .
#Text=The only other Knick to reach double figures was Cole Aldrich .
#Text=He started at center and finished with 11 points and 14 rebounds .
#Text=It marked his third double - double of the season .
#Text=With all the injuries and only two players reaching double - digit points , the Knicks just did n't have the offensive fire power to stay within reach .
#Text=The Pistons ' next game will be at home against the Sacramento Kings on Sunday , while the Knicks will be at home against the Milwaukee Bucks on Sunday .
